Web-Dev Battle: Expense Manager Project Solution BY RITU JALAN

DESCRIPTION: This is the solution to the Expense Manager Site

Extract the files from expense_manager.zip.

_____________________________________________Folder Structure__________________________________________________
	
	
expense_manager/
	css/ (contains all the css files)
	 	bootstrap.css
		bootstrap.min.css
		style.css
	
	fonts/ (contains glyphicons)
	    	glyphicons-halflings-regular.eot
	    	glyphicons-halflings-regular.html
	    	glyphicons-halflings-regular.ttf
	    	glyphicons-halflings-regular.woff
	    	glyphicons-halflings-regular.woff2

	js/ (contains Bootstrap Js files.)
	     	bootstrap.js
     		bootstrap.min.js
		jquery.js
	     
	img/ (contains all images required for developing the website and user uploaded images)
	
	includes/	 
		common.php
		common_query.php
	   	footer.php
	   	header.php
		image_model.php

	database/
		expense_manager.sql(Database of the project)	
	  
index.php
login.php
login_script.php
logout_script.php
About.php
settings.php
settings-script.php
signup.php
signup_script.php
create_pg1.php
create_pg2.php
create_submit.php
expense_distribution.php
home.php
view_plan.php





____________________________________________SETUP_________________________________________________________________________________________				


1.) Start the Apache and MySQL modules using the XAMPP controller.

2.) Open the phpMyAdmin and create a database "expense_manager". 

3.) Import the expense_manager.sql file present in database folder of the zip folder.

4.) Open the htdocs folder in the xampp folder. Copy paste the folder expense_manager.

5.) Open the browser (chrome), type localhost/expense_manager and you should see the index page of the website.

